content: The list of 39 victims of the Xinyu fire was released, including 31 students, 1 teacher, 1 worker, and 6 hotel staff. Most of them were born in the 2000s, most of them were in their 20s, about 10 girls and 20 boys.

content:
On January 25, Shanghai. A strange man suddenly broke into a clothing store and started to smash and destroy things, demanding that the woman close the store and leave, and slapped and pushed her.
After the case was filed, it was learned that the man was a merchant in a nearby store.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
It was reported online that on January 14, an employee of Sanqi Interactive Entertainment died suddenly due to long hours of high-intensity work. On January 24, his family went to the company to defend their rights.
According to the information on the Internet, the employee had to pay for the tuition of two children and the mortgage. In addition to his own work, he had to take on additional outsourced work until three in the morning. He could only rest for four hours a day, and had to send his children to school and catch the subway at seven the next morning.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
“Palu’s life is also life”
Recently, a game called "Phantom Beast Parlu" quickly became popular in China. In the game, players can collect phantom beasts called "Palu" and send them to produce and work for them.
The "Palu" in the game made many players empathize with their identity and situation as workers, and began to make jokes about it.
What's more, when a host treated Palu kindly during the live broadcast, he was immediately compared to a "teacher" by the players.

On January 26, the Zhengzhou Municipal Government Supervision Office notified all units to participate in a "2023 Provincial Key Livelihood Issues Questionnaire Survey" on Dahe.com to get good reviews.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
On January 22, a teacher at a boarding school in Puyang County, Henan Province, said that they had recently received a notice from the school, requiring each boarding school to arrange for one person to stay up all night and patrol every 10 minutes. The notice also pointed out that surveillance evidence would be collected every day to verify the personnel's adherence to night patrols.
School staff told reporters that "safety is no small matter, and it is not too much to go to each office every ten minutes."
This caused netizens to complain

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On January 26, at Jiangqiao, Jiading, Shanghai, a police officer was punishing an illegal electric bicycle when he found a passerby filming it. He approached and questioned the passerby, saying that he would take the passerby "inside to have a chat." The passerby responded calmly and legally maintained his law enforcement supervision rights.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On January 25, Jiangsu Province, a man held up his veterans’ preferential card and filmed a video to ask for help, saying that he was a Tibetan veteran and had lent 110,000 yuan to the grain management office in Shizhai Town, Fengxian County in 2017. Unexpectedly, the grain management office went bankrupt and has not repaid the debt to date. He had no choice but to film a video to seek help.

name: 李老师不是你老师
